title: Stick Navigation Chart, Before 1950
medium: Carved wooden sticks, cowrie shells and twine lashing
creditline: Department of Anthropology, National Museum of Natural History, Smithsonian Institution, E432083
description: Square shaped stick navigation chart. Wooden sticks tied at intervals with brown twine. Cowrie shells attached at intersection of certain sticks. Sticks broken in 7 places. Some breaks wrapped with white string. Donor commented she had used string to hold broken sticks together.

tombstone.epitaph: Stick Navigation Chart, Before 1950. Carved wooden sticks, cowrie shells and twine lashing. Department of Anthropology, National Museum of Natural History, Smithsonian Institution, E432083. 15.2012.35.
